<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 22 at 5:26AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...POCKETS OF FREEZING RAIN POSSIBLE PRIOR TO DAYBREAK...
Light sleet and spotty freezing rain will impact eastern
Rensselaer County and Bennington County Vermont prior to 8 am.
At the onset, surface temperatures will be near or slightly below
freezing. Some pockets of freezing rain are possible over the
higher terrain.
A trace to a light glaze could result in icy spots, especially
any untreated surfaces including sidewalks, overpasses, bridges,
exit and entrance ramps. Temperatures are expected to warm above
freezing through the morning hours.</description>
